CHIKUNGUNYA - INDIAN OCEAN UPDATE (23): SEQUELAE, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Sat 19 Aug 2007
From: Sajith Kumar <rsajith@dataone.in>

Following the chikungunya epidemic in which millions have been
affected in Kerala [India] and other states, we are now witnessing an
unusual amount of joint and skin diseases in our patients. We would
like to have some light on the patterns and incidence of these in
previous epidemics.
--
Dr. Sajith Kumar
Kottayam, Kerala, India
<rsajith@dataone.in>
[It's not unreasonable that, with these huge outbreaks, we could be
seeing rare sequelae. - Mod.LM]
[Dr. Kumar raises an interesting question. Given the large number of
chikungunya virus infections across the Indian Ocean, including
India, it would be valuable to know whether sequelae are being
observed. ProMED requests that any relevant information be provided. - Mod.TY]
